SD=Customer Case Management
CR= Customer Case Management Plan
BQs=Rules Performance     
Manage customer case handling, track the effectiveness and impact of case resolution. Evaluate and confirm that the decision making rules and thresholds are well balanced in terms of equitable determination with general customer and merchant acceptance of the process. Ensure and that sufficient and appropriately trained resources are available 
Customer case handling is assessed over a period and the rules and thresholds guiding resolution decisions recalibrated
Track and assess case load and resolution activity - allocate resources as necessary to optimize case resolution performance
CR - Customer Case Management Plan					BQ 1 - Rules 			BQ 2 - Performance		
Cr	Up	Ec	Rq	Re	Up	Rq	Re	Up	Rq	Re
CrCR Create the management plan for customer case handling
UpCR Update aspects of the customer case handling management plan
EcCR Accept, reject, etc. aspects of the management plan
RqCR Request manual intervention with the plan (e.g. reprioritize activities)
ReCR Retrieve details about the customer case handling management plan
UpBQ Update details of the case resolution criterion
RqBQ Request manual intervention in the case resolution rules (e.g. provide evidence of issues with suggested improvements for consideration)
ReBQ Retrieve details about the customer case criterion
UpBQ Update performance analysis related information
RqBQ Request manual intervention in unit performance analysis (e.g. provide mitigating details to qualify an assessment)
ReBQ Retrieve details about business unit performance assessment activity